{"questionId":"12335","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>In a reforested area of pine trees, heights of trees planted in a specific year seem to follow a normal distribution. A sample of 100 such trees is selected to test the validity of this hypothesis. The results of measuring tree heights, to the nearest centimetre, are recorded in the first two columns of the table below.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/2ede1f6198c699a9c21c7a8196287849b4a7ce7f.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>In order to test for the goodness of fit, the test statistic was calculated to be 1.0847. Show how this was done.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p class=\"indent1\">The test statistic is a <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"{\\chi ^2}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msup> <mi>χ</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp;variable. Hence&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p class=\"indent1\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"{\\chi ^2} = \\sum {\\frac{{{{\\left( {{f_e} - {f_o}} \\right)}^2}}}{{{f_e}}}}&nbsp; = \\frac{{{{\\left( {6 - 6} \\right)}^2}}}{6} + \\frac{{{{\\left( {9 - 11} \\right)}^2}}}{9} +&nbsp; \\ldots \\frac{{{{\\left( {5 - 6} \\right)}^2}}}{5}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msup> <mi>χ</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mo>∑</mo> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mi>f</mi> <mi>e</mi> </msub> </mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi>f</mi> <mi>o</mi> </msub> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mi>f</mi> <mi>e</mi> </msub> </mrow> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mn>6</mn> <mo>−</mo> <mn>6</mn> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> <mn>6</mn> </mfrac> <mo>+</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mn>9</mn> <mo>−</mo> <mn>11</mn> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> <mn>9</mn> </mfrac> <mo>+</mo> <mo>…</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mn>5</mn> <mo>−</mo> <mn>6</mn> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> <mn>5</mn> </mfrac> </math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p class=\"indent1\">= 1.0847&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p class=\"indent1\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12335","referenceCode":"EXM.2.AHL.TZ0.27d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"In order to test for the goodness of fit, the test statistic was calculated to be 1.0847. Show how this was done.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses, chi squared, gof, t-test","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.12—Data collection, reliability and validity tests"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}